Last year, hip-hop superstar and humanitarian Akon was named as the recipient of the 2016 Global Good Award at the BET Awards. In 2014, Akon co-founded Akon Lighting Africa. Now, he s set to make a turn at the first annual African Leaders 4 Change Awards (ALCA), which will be held in September at Nelson Mandela Square in Sandton, north of Johannesburg. The ceremony will honour and recognise initiatives that have made a difference around the continent. These are initiatives that have shown verve for adding a positive, meaningful impact on African lives without seeking a financial reward. Akon will host the award show to be broadcast on more than 15 channels across the African continent. Categories includes wildlife preservation, leadership and education. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.